The _[Integer.parseInt](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Integer.html#parseInt(java.lang.String))_ method will throw a _[NumberFormatException](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/NumberFormatException.html)_ if the string does not contain a parsable integer.

You can utilize a _[try-catch](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/exceptions/index.html)_ block to capture the thrown exception.

The syntax is as follows.

```java
try {

} catch (ExceptionType name) {

}
```

When a statement within the _try_-block throws an exception, the block is exited and entered at the _catch_-block.

You can access the _Exception_ object via the name declared at the start of the _catch_-block.

Here is an example of your code, utilizing a _try-catch_ to validate the input value.

```java
