I took this sample for autodetection code [from here](https://github.com/vgmoose/JWiiLoad/blob/master/src/JWiiLoad.java#L346-L358)

Try to increase the timeout. I used about 5000ms, this helped me.
In case you don&#39;t want to wait 5000ms * 254 = 21 minutes, try also this code with parallel pinging to the addresses:

    public static void getNetworkIPs() {
        final byte[] ip;
        try {
            ip = InetAddress.getLocalHost().getAddress();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return;     // exit method, otherwise &quot;ip might not have been initialized&quot;
        }
        
        for(int i=1;i&lt;=254;i++) {
            final int j = i;  // i as non-final variable cannot be referenced from inner class
            new Thread(new Runnable() {   // new thread for parallel execution
                public void run() {
                    try {
                        ip[3] = (byte)j;
                        InetAddress address = InetAddress.getByAddress(ip);
                        String output = address.toString().substring(1);
                        if (address.isReachable(5000)) {
                            System.out.println(output + &quot; is on the network&quot;);
                        } else {
                            System.out.println(&quot;Not Reachable: &quot;+output);
                        }
                    } catch (Exception e) {
                        e.printStackTrace();
                    }
                }
            }).start();     // dont forget to start the thread
        }
    }

