You can&#39;t update array&#39;s element using `for-each`. This is only for reading.

```java
public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
    int[] marks = new int[3];

    for (int i = 0; i &lt; marks.length; i++)
        marks[i] = sc.nextInt();

    for (int ele : marks)
        System.out.print(ele + &quot; &quot;);
}
```

The error is in your first for-loop.  You are assigning _nextInt_ to _ele_.  
Rather, the _marks_ array is what you need to assign _ele_ to.

```java
for (int ele : marks) {
    ele = sc.nextInt();
}
```

Instead of a loop, you can just assign the 3 values to their indices.

```java
marks[0] = sc.nextInt();
marks[1] = sc.nextInt();
marks[2] = sc.nextInt();
```

